# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Type should be one of the following:
# * feat (new feature)
# * fix (bug fix)
# * docs (documentation)
# * style (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
# * refactor (refactoring production code)
# * test (adding tests, refactoring test; no production code change)
# * chore (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc; no production code change)
#
# Scope: The area of the codebase affected (e.g., config, routing, docs)
# Subject: Short description (imperative tone, no period)
# Body: Detailed explanation of what changed and why
# Footer: Breaking changes, issue references, etc.
